article.headline: Dartmouth 69, Columbia 62
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Leon Pattman scored 27 points in 26 minutes to help the Big Green win 69-62 Friday over Columbia. Pattman made 8-of-11 shots from the field, 3-of-4 from outside the arc and 8-of-9 from the foul line for Dartmouth (6-20 overall, 4-9 Ivy League). John Baumann had 14 points and nine rebounds for Columbia (11-15, 4-9 Ivy), which lost to Dartmouth for the second time this season. Dartmouth shot 57.7 percent from the field and made 6-of-11 3-point shots while building a 41-31 halftime lead. Trailing by as many as 15 points in the second half with less than 5 minutes left, Columbia got a pair of 3-pointers from Brett Loscalzo in a 15-3 run to close within 65-62 with 1:11 to play. It stayed that way until Pattman put the game away by going 4-for-4 from the foul line in the final 14 seconds.
